synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involved using lithium sulfide (Li2S), phosphorus pentasulfide (P2S5), and lithium iodide (LiI) as starting materials, mixing them in specific molar ratios, ball milling the mixture for 40 hours, drying it to obtain a sulfide glass, and further heating the glass at 190Â°C for 10 hours to produce glass ceramics.
